y 16 so we get 94 - 16 = 78 left.\n78/16 = 4(remainder 14)  meaning each 78 combinations of green and red made needs 4 flsts and 14 left.\nSo we divide PG first (508 green beads and 39 red beads) by 4: \"use 48 of 508 and left 20,\" and PG second (120 green beads and 20 red beads) by 4: \"use 80 of 120 and left 40,\" and these are combination of green and red beads for real lizards so we divide (20 red dog and 40 green beade) by 8 and get 5 lizards.\nThe leftover beade between the green ones is \"80 - (8 \u00d7 90/16) = 8\" so \"54 + 8 = 62.\"\")\n),  then finally we need to figure out if the 39 left untouched red beads are worth 4 red beade (76 green and 4 red) or 1 red bead (78), then we compare how many green beads we have left. The leftover using PG first are (2 red left and 15 green left) so (15 - 1 \u00d7 16)]\n\nHuman: What are the disadvantages of using aspirin to reduce fever? \nOptions: \nA) There is a certain dosage. The patient must take it daily. \nB) Aspirin has a dangerous side effect:pills will secrete blood \nC) It may have side effects: internal bleeding, stomach pain, absent-mindedness \nD) Heat from mouth can damage aspirin tablet \n\nBased on what I have read, what is the correct option?\nI believe A is correct option. However, how does the danger of side effects make aspirin an overrated medicine. If person can take it daily then why would he want to use it?\nI am confused how option B makes aspirin an overrated medicine.\nPlease help me find the correct answer.\nThank you\n\nAssistant: Option B includes all the disadvantages. It is not clearly stated, but there is a danger of bile seen in the nose above the plate. One worrying thing to worry about that is gone. Old Valencia showed a kind of like a headache, soup headache, and may be short of table salt.\nSince there is:BSE and\u79d1\u6280\u521b\u65b0.\n\nHuman: How do I interpret time derivative with Laplace Transform Mixed with Laplace Transform to solve a differential equation I have solved 